	"title": {
		"rendered": "Course Introduction"
	},
	"content": {
		"rendered": "<p>This course teaches students to use Adobe Dreamweaver CC, the industry standard web design application. Students will design and author a web site that is user-friendly, portable, and easy to modify. Topics of this course include the use of tables for flexible layout and design, Cascading Style Sheets (CSS), selected JavaScript behaviors, the appropriate use of color, and effective navigation strategies. At the completion of the course, students will have designed, created, and tested a Web site.<\/p>\n<p>While web page developers need to understand HTML (Hypertext Markup Language), they should also be knowledgeable about the use of WYSIWYG editors. Macromedia Dreamweaver is an industry standard, leading web development application for Web design, maintenance, and site management. Throughout the course, the student will use the WYSIWYG capabilities of Dreamweaver while still editing the underlying HTML code when necessary.<\/p>\n<p><script src=\"https:\/\/dev01.inside-out-project.com\/iop_app\/iop_lp_widget_v-1.0.0.4\/iop_lp_widget_pods_template.js\"><\/script><\/p>\n",
		"protected": false
	},
