				"post_title": "From The Instructor",
				"post_content": "<p>The primary learning objective of this course is to expand a deeper understanding of web application development while gaining a deeper knowledge of HTML5. This course has two per-requisites, WEB-100 and being able to use a computer and web browser. We keep things simple because we truly want \u201cEveryone\u201d to learn! Under \u201cModules\u201d the entire course has been laid out in a proprietary order that will guide you through all the learning objectives. Each of the learning objectives has one or more exercise and\/or an assessment quiz that you will do to work through the course. You can track your progress in the \u201cGrades\u201d section of Canvas. You should expect to spend 3-5 hours per a week in this course. An important technique, if you find yourself struggling with the material, is to jump back and re-do an earlier section. Having a solid understanding of all the ideas in the course is more important than getting through the course successfully. As the Instructor, I will monitor the \u201cHelp Forum\u201d from time to time, but for this course to scale, it will be important that the participants in the course help each other. You must say \u2018hi\u2019 to your fellow students in the \u201cIntroduce Yourself\u201d discussion.<\/p>\r\n<p><script src=\"https:\/\/dev01.inside-out-project.com\/iop_app\/iop_lp_widget_v-1.0.0.4\/iop_lp_widget_pods_template.js\"><\/script><\/p>",
